          <div id="tabs-wrapper" class="clearfix">                                <h1 class="with-tabs">batch resizing with fixed w:h ratio?</h1>
                              </div>                                                  <div class="clearfix">
              <div class="region region-content">
    <div id="block-system-main" class="block block-system clearfix">

    
  <div class="content">
    <div id="node-27491" class="node node-question">

  
      
      <span class="submitted">September 25, 2012 - 20:31 — <span class="username">buzz buzz</span></span>
  
  <div class="content clearfix">
    <div class="form-item form-type-item">
  <label>Useful? </label>
 
</div>
<div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p>the normal resize function in gimp always keeps the width:height ration while resizing(unless you specify it).but i could not find any plugins with this feature.are there any plugins or scripts that can do this?please answer.</p>
<p>PS:an example-let's say the image is 700x200 pixels,so the ratio is 7:2...now if i change it from 700 to 70,in normal gimp resize,the other dimension changes to 20,but for the plugins,it remains at 200.is there any plugin or script that can do this kind of resize?</p>
</div></div></div><div class="field field-name-field-related field-type-node-reference field-label-above"><div class="field-label">Related Content:&nbsp;</div><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><a href="21834">Batch watermarking and resizing</a></div></div></div><div class="view view-question-answers-best-answers- view-id-question_answers_best_answers_ view-display-id-entity_view_1 view-dom-id-9519f5dcd43bf3db15bcaa0431096314">
      
  
  
